SALES OVERVIEW

In [25]:
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'], errors='coerce')
df['YearMonth'] = df['Date'].dt.to_period('M')
sales_over_time = df.groupby('Date')['Amount'].sum().reset_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='Amount', data=sales_over_time)
plt.title('Total Sales Over Time')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Total Sales')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

PRODUCT ANALYSIS

In [10]:
order_product_df = df.groupby('Order ID')['Category'].apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x)).reset_index()
product_combinations = order_product_df['Category'].str.get_dummies(sep=', ')
product_comb_matrix = product_combinations.T.dot(product_combinations)
np.fill_diagonal(product_comb_matrix.values, 0)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))
sns.heatmap(product_comb_matrix, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap='YlGnBu')
plt.title('Product Combinations Heatmap')
plt.xlabel('Product')
plt.ylabel('Product')
plt.show()

BUSINESS INSIGHTS

Based on the analysis, here are some accountable insights and recommendations to optimize sales strategies, improve customer satisfaction, and enhance overall business performance.

Insights and Recommendations¶

  1. Sales Trends and Performance:

    • Insight: There is a noticeable trend in monthly sales, indicating peak periods.
    • Recommendation: Capitalize on peak sales periods with targeted promotions and inventory stocking.

  2. Product Preferences:

    • Insight: Certain product categories and sizes are more popular.
    • Recommendation: Focus marketing efforts on popular categories and sizes, ensure adequate stock levels for these items.

  3. Fulfillment Methods:

    • Insight: Some fulfillment methods are more effective in delivering orders promptly.
    • Recommendation: Invest in the more effective fulfillment methods and streamline processes for the less effective ones to reduce delivery times and improve customer satisfaction.

  4. Customer Behavior:

    • Insight: There are patterns in customer purchase frequencies and preferences based on location.
    • Recommendation: Tailor marketing campaigns and promotions based on customer segmentation, focusing on high-value and frequent buyers.

  5. Geographical Distribution:

    • Insight: Sales are concentrated in specific states and cities.
    • Recommendation: Optimize logistics and inventory distribution in high-sales areas to reduce shipping times and costs. Expand marketing efforts in lower-sales regions to increase market penetration.

Deliverables¶

  1. Comprehensive Analysis Report:

    • Summarizes key findings, insights, and recommendations.
    • Includes visualizations to support the findings.

  2. Visualizations:

    • Charts and graphs illustrating sales trends, product analysis, fulfillment methods, customer segmentation, and geographical distribution.

  3. Business Insights:

    • Detailed insights on product preferences, customer behavior, and geographical sales distribution.
    • Actionable recommendations for improving sales strategies, inventory management, and customer service.

  4. Recommendations:

    • Strategies to optimize business operations, enhance customer experience, and drive revenue growth.
